Class AbstractElement<E,C1,C2>

java.lang.Object
  context.arch.discoverer.component.AbstractElement<E,C1,C2>
Type Parameters:
E - class of return of extractElement(ComponentDescription); i.e. the format of the element that we want to compare
C1 - class of the first comparison argument to AbstractComparison
C2 - class of the second comparison argument to AbstractComparison; this is usually set to be the same as C1.

getValueCodex

public java.lang.String getValueCodex()
When passing value through the query system, it could to be converted to a string. This method is called to get the string representation. Default is to return the toString() method of the getValue(). If value is a complex object, then this method should be overridden to allow sufficient conversion.

Returns:
See Also:
getValueDataObject()

getValueDataObject

public DataObject getValueDataObject()
When passing value through the query system, it could to be converted to a DataObject. This is especially useful for complex value objects. The system would check if this is set first, then check getValueCodex(). It should be overridden by the subclass to set it if used.

Returns:
null by default, otherwise a DataObject representing the value if set.
